Transatlantic Says It Will Consider Validus Bid ‘In Due Course’

-- B y   B r o o k e   S u t h e r l a n d
-- 
2011-07-13T11:46:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-13/transatlantic-says-it-will-consider-validus-bid-in-due-course-.html
Transatlantic Holdings Inc. (TRH) , the
reinsurer that agreed to merge with Allied World Assurance
Company Holdings AG, said it will weigh an unsolicited rival bid
from  Validus Holdings Ltd. (VR)   The board “will carefully consider and evaluate the
Validus proposal in due course and will inform Transatlantic
stockholders of its position,” Bermuda-based Transatlantic said
today in a statement distributed by  Business Wire .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brooke Sutherland in New York at 
 bsutherland5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  